# =============================================================================
# JIRANIRIDE FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================
# These variables are used by the React frontend (Vite)
# IMPORTANT: All VITE_* variables are EXPOSED to the browser!
# Never put sensitive credentials here.
# =============================================================================

# Supabase Configuration (Public - Safe to expose)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=YOUR_SUPABASE_URL
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# =============================================================================
# M-PESA CREDENTIALS - NOT STORED HERE!
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️ M-Pesa credentials are NOT in this .env file for security reasons.
# They are stored as Supabase Edge Function secrets (server-side only).
#
# Why?
# - Frontend .env variables are visible in the browser
# - Anyone could steal your M-Pesa credentials from DevTools
# - Edge Function secrets are encrypted and server-side only
#
# To set M-Pesa credentials, use the Supabase CLI:
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_CONSUMER_KEY="your_key"
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_CONSUMER_SECRET="your_secret"
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_PASSKEY="your_passkey"
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_SHORTCODE="174379"
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_ENVIRONMENT="sandbox"
#   supabase secrets set MPESA_CALLBACK_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co/functions/v1/mpesa-callback"
#
# Or use the setup script:
#   ./setup-mpesa.sh
#
# See MPESA_SETUP.md for detailed instructions.
# =============================================================================
